Version: 1.1 · Last updated: 2026-05-14 · See "Document Review & Corrections" at end.

Document Purpose

This document defines the technical system architecture for AirportFaster based on the approved Product Architecture Definition, BRD, and UX/Product Flows.

It translates business and UX requirements into an implementation-ready architecture covering:

* Frontend architecture
* Backend architecture
* Core business services
* Database domains
* Authentication and permissions
* Search and booking engine
* Pricing and availability engine
* Payments and refunds
* Notifications
* Flight data integration
* SEO / AEO / AGO rendering strategy
* Admin dashboard architecture
* Security and scalability

⸻

1. Architecture Overview

AirportFaster will be built as a modular web platform with a strong operational backend and SEO-first public frontend.

Core Architecture Style

Recommended initial architecture:

Modular Monolith with clear domain boundaries.

This is the best starting model because AirportFaster needs speed, control, and operational flexibility without the early complexity of microservices.

The codebase should be structured so that services can later be extracted into independent services if scale requires it.

