Document Review & Corrections (v1.1)

Reviewed 2026-05-14. Architecture preserved; the following corrections apply and override earlier text where they conflict.

1. Canonical backend modules (21). The module list in section 8 is extended to separate three modules that were previously folded in or omitted: Stripe Webhooks (distinct from Payments), AI SEO Engine, and AI Translation Engine. Full canonical list: Auth & RBAC, Airports, Services, Search, Availability, Pricing, Bookings, Payments, Stripe Webhooks, Suppliers, Operations, Incidents, Refunds, Notifications, Flight Data, CMS/SEO, AI SEO Engine, AI Translation Engine, Analytics, Audit Logs, Settings.

2. AI draft systems ARE in MVP. Section 35 ("Not in MVP") is corrected: the AI SEO draft system and AI translation draft system are IN the MVP (draft-only; AI never auto-publishes; Draft → Review → Edit → Approve → Publish). Only fully automated AI operations / AI auto-publishing remain post-MVP. Section 34's MVP backend list is extended to include the AI SEO Engine and AI Translation Engine modules and the Stripe Webhooks module.

3. Stack is now canonical, not optional. Backend = Fastify (not "Fastify or Express"). ORM = Prisma (not "Prisma or Drizzle"). These are binding decisions (DECISIONS.md D-003).

4. Payment provider = Stripe. All "payment gateway" references mean Stripe. Payment state is driven exclusively by signature-validated webhook events; every event is persisted in stripe_webhook_events for idempotency and audit. AirportFaster is merchant of record (D-006); the customer is charged at checkout (D-007).

5. Pricing engine. The engine supports two modes per airport/service: fixed price or supplier cost + markup (D-008). Pricing is snapshotted onto the booking at booking time. "Future dynamic pricing" = AI/algorithmic pricing only, post-MVP.

6. Data domains. Section 9's data domains are now fully specified in the Database Architecture & Entity Relationship Design document, which adds the previously missing tables: stripe_webhook_events, settlements / settlement_lines / payouts (merchant-of-record), ai_generation_logs, translation_jobs, ai_prompt_templates, content_approval_workflow, sitemap_logs, and cancellation_policies. That document is the data-layer source of truth.

7. Recommended next documents (section 36). "Database Architecture & Entity Relationship Design" is now complete. Remaining priority docs: API Specification, UI Design System, QA Test Plan. The Development Sprint Plan also now exists.
